sec.p:
A linear or a linearized system of a vehicle dynamic model can be written in the following form:
(8)[M]{y··}+[C]{y·}+[K]{y}=[Dw]{zw}+[Ddw]{z·w}
where [M], [C] and [K] are inertia, damping and stiffness matrices, respectively, [Dw] and [Ddw] are track irregularity displacement and velocity input matrices, respectively, and {zw} and {y} are the track irregularity input and system response vector, respectively.
